statement:
Let

\begin{align*}f(x) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \left[ \left\{ \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{2+\left( 1+\frac{x-1}{n} \right)^3} + \frac{1}{2+\left( 1+\frac{2(x-1)}{n} \right)^3} + \ldots \right.\right.\end{align*}

\begin{align*}\ldots + \left.\left.\frac{1}{2+\left( 1+\frac{(n-1)(x-1)}{n} \right)^3} \right\} \frac{x-1}{n} \right]\end{align*}
where \emph{x} $\geq$ 0. Find the equation of the tangent line to the
graph \emph{y} = \emph{f}(\emph{x}) at \emph{x} = 1.

hints:
Recall that the general form of a (left) Riemann sum is

\begin{align*}\int_a^b f(y)\,dy = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \sum_{j=0}^{n-1} \Delta y\,f(y_j),\end{align*}

where $y_j = a + j\Delta y$ and $\Delta y = \frac{b-a}{n}$.
